    {
      "id": "a1aa58ce_b40e4dc3",
      "file_path": "integrity-audit/src/test/java/org/onap/policy/common/ia/DefaultLoggingPatternTest.java",
      "patchset_number": 4,
      "line": 41,
      "message": "On first question, good question, the answer is that it works fine for Logger too. I added a test case for it.\n\nThe logback.xml was there before this review but, I agree, it could cause problems especially as you can't guarantee what order the various logback.xml files are in the classpath. Log4j will use the first one it comes across, something I know from having spent many hours checking why logging changes I was making in a certain logback.xml were not showing up where I needed them.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 2787,
        "name": "Liam Fallon",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "liam.fallon@est.tech",
        "username": "liamfallon"
      },
      "updated": "2019-12-06 14:40:27.000000000",
